The paper introduces a new framework for expressing conditional preferences, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The framework is based on Datalog, a declarative logic programming language commonly used in databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms and implementation, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
